@node NOTICE "Notice to the using of AmiStart"

    @{b}NOTICE:@{ub}

        This version was compiled for mc68020 (no FPU)  and above, i think thats no problem.

        Version 0.56:
            It is recommended to rise the stack size (16384 bytes for example),
            this is important because of the recursive removing from directorys (16384 is just a
            suggestion, i don't know the exact value).

            The guigfx.library is not longer optional since Version 0.56 uses it for Icon handling.

        Version 0.59:
            There is a popup-menu build in (see @{"requirements" link REQUIREMENTS}), this needs the Right-Mousebutton
            handling to be changed, but thats has nearly no effect, you could close Layers as before
            by clicking the RMB, but this must be done a very short time, longer pressing down the RMB cause
            to popup the PopUp menu.

            MUI is not longer optional, coz i use it for requesters to enable more keyboard shortcodes.

            Some changes are done in the transparency handling, see @{"USAGE/Others" link OTHERS}

            WARNING: AmiStart has massive problems on 256 Color wb-views, no idea why

            AmiStart can only be started once, a new call will stop a running AmiStart task

        Version 0.60:
            AmiStart uses its own border colors now instead of the system entries, you could select values for them in the
            global prefs now (named Shine and Shadow color).

        Version 0.61
            Removed the ToolTypes @{"AUTOACTIVATE TIMEOUT MOREUNSHARP and FORCEREFRESH" link TOOLTYPES},
            this ponits are now selectable in the Global Settings in the "Misc" section-popup
            look in the ToolTypes section for a description of this stuff

        Version 0.62:
            Removed the ToolType @{"JUMPQUALIFIER" link TOOLTYPES}, but you can setup this Qualifier in
            the Global Settings/Misc section.

        Version 0.64:
            using the successor of the older ttrender.library named ttengine.library, the ttengine.library supports aga so the USETTRENDER
            ToolType was removed. Note by default AmiStart needs #?.ttf fonts to be installed into the fonts:_truetype_outlines drawer, but you can
            use a global ENV-Variable named TTFPATH to setup an different location.

@endnode

